---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Stay or Go · Ennea Evolution"
  description="Some decisions can't be made with a list. The deadlock isn't made of facts, and there's a way to move that doesn't require one more list."
>
  <div style="--accent:#2BA1A3;">
    <!-- PANEL 1 · white · hero -->
    <section class="panel">
      <div class="container narrow">
        <p class="eyebrow">Personal Work</p>
        <h1>Some decisions can't be made with a list.</h1>
        <p class="lead">A marriage. A faith. A career. You know the question by heart because you've been carrying it for years. You could make a case for either side. Some nights, you do.</p>
        <p>Here's the good news hiding inside that: you're not indecisive. If facts were going to settle this, they would have by now, because you have all the facts. The deadlock isn't made of facts. Which means there's a way to move that doesn't require one more list, and I've helped a lot of people find it.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PANEL 2 · tint #CCD8DE · inner voice -->
    <section class="panel tint-band" style="--tint:#CCD8DE;">
      <div class="container narrow">
        <h3>You might recognize this</h3>
        <div class="inner-voice" style="margin-bottom:-1.5rem;">
          <p>I can argue both sides in my sleep. I've had years of practice.</p>
          <p>Today the answer feels obvious. It felt obvious yesterday too, the other way.</p>
          <p>Maybe something will happen that makes the decision for me.</p>
          <p>I've gotten very good at not finishing the thought.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PANEL 3 · white -->
    <section class="panel">
      <div class="container narrow">
        <h3>Why the question stays open</h3>
        <p>Staying undecided is protecting you from something. As long as the question stays open, nothing has to be grieved and nothing is final. The middle is painful, but it's the one place you don't have to give anything up.</p>
        <p>That's not weakness. It's very human. It's also not where you have to live.</p>
        <p>What's been missing from the process isn't a fact. It's the part of you that rarely gets a vote when a decision matters this much. The mind stays busy running the arguments because thinking feels like progress and feeling feels risky.</p>

        <h3 style="margin-top:2.5rem;">What the work is</h3>
        <p>Nobody can make this decision for you, and you wouldn't trust it if they did. What I can do is help you hear the parts of you the internal arguing has talked over.</p>
        <p>We let both sides be heard all the way through. Not just the case for staying and the case for going, but what it would feel like to live inside each one. Sometimes the thing you've been afraid to imagine gets less frightening once you follow it all the way to the end.</p>
        <p>The goal isn't an answer someone hands you. It's your own judgment back, so the choice is truly yours.</p>
        <div class="photo-block" style="--block:#CCD8DE; margin-top:2.5rem;">
          <div class="photo">
            <img src="/img/stay-path.jpg" alt="A single path curving on through an avenue of old trees" width="1400" height="787" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 style="margin-top:2.5rem;">What changes</h3>
        <p>The question stops running your life. The middle-of-the-night arguing gets quieter, because the conversation finally includes the part of you it was always missing.</p>
        <blockquote class="pullquote">People who stay, stay differently. People who go, go cleaner.</blockquote>
        <p>The difference isn't the outcome. It's that you finally trust the one who chose it.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="hairline-gold" />

    <!-- PANEL 4 · white · close -->
    <section class="panel center">
      <div class="container narrow">
        <h3>Start here</h3>
        <p>You don't have to know the answer. You only have to be tired of the question.</p>
        <a href="/get-started" class="btn" style="margin-top:0.5rem;">Schedule a Free 15-Minute Call</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>
